For each experiment (naïve and trained participants), a separate second-level analysis was conducted in MATLAB (SPM12) using a flexible factorial design including all four experimental conditions. 
For the trained participants, condition-specific beta estimates were extracted from the identified regions of interest (ROIs). 
The same ROIs were then used to extract contrast estimates from the corresponding contrast images of the naïve participants. 
An R script was used to compare the extracted values between the trained and naïve groups.

